{
  "stem": "13469.5",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But there were a number of potatoes in each large urn that they had-- [DUTCH] as they call them in Dutch-- large urn, which the soup was-- you know, Rudy and his friends, they would go over to the kitchen outside the camp, and they'd bring over this urn.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And then we'd all have to queue up, and he'd dish out the thing.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And everybody would, of course, say, you know, stir it before you give it to us, because otherwise you would just get the water.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But anyway, he could stir it, and he could still give everybody just the water.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And he could keep the bits of potato and turnips in the bottom for his friends and relatives, if you like, kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "He-- he knows he did all these sort of things, he's not particularly proud of them.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And-- and in-- in some ways it's difficult to defend doing things like that, except that you got the mentality of everybody for themselves in-- in the camp-- where everybody tried to do whatever they could to stay alive, basically.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "The same-- which was in the evening, we would get black bread, about an inch and a half-- about that thick sliced bread.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Basically, we had a big piece of black bread, and that was supposed to be for eight people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So first of all, it was tricky cutting it into eight equal pieces.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Everybody would demand that they had the first choice, kind of thing, of each piece, kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And so there was a lot of chicanery going on with that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And then you could to do things where Rudy, me, and my father, we would say, we want a three-- we want a piece for three.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
